title: Latest commit: bf1e2631281e1e439533f2abcf1e99a7b2f9552a on master can't be built into a working geth on Mac
body:
#### System information

Geth version: `1.7.0-unstable`
OS & Version: OSX
Commit hash : bf1e2631281e1e439533f2abcf1e99a7b2f9552a
Mac version: macOS Sierra version 10.12.4
go version: go1.8.3 darwin/amd64


#### Expected behaviour
The commit can successfully build a geth binary which can be up and running without problem.

#### Actual behaviour
Running the geth built form the bf1e2631281e1e439533f2abcf1e99a7b2f9552a commit throws exceptions at runtime.

#### Steps to reproduce the behaviour
1. go to <ethereum_home>
2. git checkout bf1e2631281e1e439533f2abcf1e99a7b2f9552a
3. go install ./...
4. geth --fast
5. wait for a few seconds.
